ranslate across industry boundaries into print, video, film, television, packaging, advertising, digital design, and more. Typographic Design provides insight, information, and practical instruction for every step in the process, from concept to execution. Topics include: Letterforms, syntax, and legibility Communication and the typographic message Evolution and technology of typography Typographic design processes, and using the grid The book also contains case studies that illustrate the successful use of typography, demonstrating the impact of good type on the overall design, and a listing of type specimens that exhibit good communication through good design. Words are an important part of the human condition, and presentation can have a major impact on the message. Graphic designers must be able to manipulate type to convey precisely what's intended, and Typographic Design is a comprehensive guide to mastery"--cProvided by publisher.  a"Provides a comprehensive overview of every aspect of designing with type"--cProvided by publisher.0 aOnline resource; title from digital title page (viewed on November 11, 2014).  a29 57 0aGraphic design (Typography)1 aMeggs, Philip B.,eauthor.1 aDay, Ben,eauthor.1 aMaxa, Sandra,eauthor.1 aSanders, Markq(Mark Allen),eauthor.403MacEwan University Accessuhttp://search.ebscohost.com/login.aspx?direct=true&scope=site&db=nlebk&db=nlabk&AN=862096z(Single User Access)  hUAINmGR_MAC_INTzEBSCOGMPp85.16  aInternet AccesswLCc1i6789621-3001lINTERNETmGR_MAC_INTp$85.16rYsYtE-RESOURCEu8/25/2015xE-BOOKzEBSCOGMP01ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n2014028294bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/308753055